'''{{ill|Nagato no Shikinaisha Ichiran|de|Nagato no Shikinaisha Ichiran|ja|長門国の式内社一覧|zh|Nagato no Shikinaisha Ichiran}}''' (長門国の式内社一覧) is a list of {{ill|Shinto Shrines|de|Shinto Shrines|ja|神社|zh|Shinto Shrines}} recorded in volumes 9 and 10, "Kami Name Register: Upper and Lower," of the {{ill|Engishiki|de|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|zh|Engishiki}} ({{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|de|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|zh|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt_ja=延喜式神名帳|lt_de=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt_zh=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}) that are classified under {{ill|Nagato Province|de|Nagato Province|ja|長門国|zh|Nagato Province}}, comprising those shrines traditionally designated as {{ill|Shikinaisha|de|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|zh|Shikinaisha}} and their associated {{ill|Candidate Shrines|de|Candidate Shrines|ja|論社|zh|Candidate Shrines}}.

In addition, it also includes shrines that existed at the time of the compilation of the Engishiki Shinmeichō but which are not recorded therein, the so‐called {{ill|Shikigaisha|de|Shikigaisha|ja|式外社|1=Shikigeisha|zh|Shikigaisha}}.

== Shikinaisha ==
In the Engishiki Shinmeichō, a total of five shrine groupings are recorded in Nagato Province – three major groups (comprising one shrine, the Myojin Taisha) and two minor groups (comprising two shrines).

